SIMPLE: scalp
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scalp
<hw>Scalp</hw> <pr>(sk⟦acr⟧lp)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Scallop</er>.]</ety> <def>A bed of oysters or mussels.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scalp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scalp
<hw>Scalp</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps akin to D. <ets>schelp</ets>
shell. Cf. <er>Scallop</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That part of the
integument of the head which is usually covered with hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By the bare <qex>scalp</qex> of Robin Hodd's fat friar,⟦br⟧
This fellow were a king for our wild faction!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A part of the skin of the head, with the hair
attached, cut or torn off from an enemy by the Indian warriors of North
America, as a token of victory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: The top; the summit.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scalp lock</b></col>, <cd>a long tuft of hair left on the
crown of the head by the warriors of some tribes of American
Indians.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scalp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scalp
<hw>Scalp</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Scalped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Scalping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of the
scalp; to cut or tear the scalp from the head of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>To remove the skin of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We must <qex>scalp</qex> the whole lid [of the eye].</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Wells.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Milling)</fld> <def>To brush the hairs or fuzz
from, as wheat grains, in the process of high milling.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scalp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Scalp
<hw>Scalp</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a small, quick profit by
slight fluctuations of the market; -- said of brokers who operate in
this way on their own account.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scalpel</ent>⟦br⟧
